window.bookSummaryJSON = "What if every memory you've ever had will be erased from your mind, and you have no choice but to carry on...powerless to stop it? <p>Alice Howland is proud of the life she worked so hard to build. At 50 years old, she's a cognitive psychology professor at Harvard and a world-renowned expert in linguistics with a successful husband and three grown children. When she begins to grow disoriented and forgetful, a tragic diagnosis changes her life - and her relationship with her family and the world - forever.</p> <p>At once beautiful and terrifying, this extraordinary debut novel by Lisa Genova is a moving and vivid depiction of life with early-onset Alzheimer's Disease that is as compelling as <i>A Beautiful Mind</i> and as unforgettable as <i>Ordinary People</i>.</p>"; 
